pull.title: build: remove -Wdeprecated-register from NOWARN flags
pull.body: The `register` keyword was deprecated in C++11, and [removed in C++17](https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/keyword/register). Now that we require C++17, we shouldn't have to suppress warnings for a non-existent feature.

non-existant feature.

events.body:
ACK 1a011b3a8285a21ca9618a35bb841d3f2d48b247

The removed suppression does not actually work on master as it is superseded by [`-Wregister`](https://clang.llvm.org/docs/DiagnosticsReference.html#wregister), at least for clang 10 -- an example for a random patch:
```
addrdb.cpp:41:5: error: ISO C++17 does not allow 'register' storage class specifier [-Wregister]
    register uint16_t randv = 0;
    ^~~~~~~~~
1 error generated.
```
